# 🏥 Clinic Queue Manager

## 📖 Description
This project is a web-based Clinic Queue Management System built using Flask.  
It allows users to add patients, manage a waiting list, and serve patients in the order they arrive.

---

## 🚀 Features
- Add new patients
- Serve patients (FIFO - First In First Out)
- Remove patients from the queue
- Undo delete using Stack (LIFO)
- View total patients served
- Timestamp for each patient

---

## 🧠 Concepts Used
- Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- Queue Data Structure (FIFO)
- Stack Data Structure (LIFO)
- Flask Web Framework
- Python datetime module

---

## 📂 Project Structure
clinic-queue-manager/
│
├── app.py
├── models.py
├── templates/
│   ├── index.html
│   └── add.html
└── README.md

---

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Install Flask:
pip install flask

2. Run the app:
python app.py

3. Open your browser:
http://127.0.0.1:5000/

---

## 💡 How It Works
Patients are added to a queue and served in the order they arrive (FIFO).  
Deleted patients are stored in a stack, allowing undo functionality (LIFO).  
Each patient is timestamped when added.

